Package edu.ncsu.csc216.pack_scheduler.util

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Queue<E>
    Generic interface for implementing a Queue list.
    Stack<E>
    The Stack interface defines the behaviors to be implemented by various list classes in the PackScheduler.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayList<E>
    The ArrayList class provides functionality for the creation of generic array list collections.
    ArrayListTest
    Tests functionality of ArrayList class
    ArrayQueue<E>
    Implements a Queue on an Arraylist and provides functions for adding items to the back of the queue, removing items from the front of the queue, checking if the queue is empty, getting the number of items in the queue, and setting the queue's capacity.
    ArrayQueueTest
    Provides suite of tests for the ArrayQueue Class
    ArrayStack<E>
    Creates an ArrayList based Stack and provides functions for pushing to the top of the stack, popping the top item off the stack, checking if the stack is empty, getting the number of items on the stack, and setting the stack's capacity.
    ArrayStackTest
    Tests the ArrayStack class
    LinkedAbstractList<E>
    Defines the state and behavior for a list of nodes.
    LinkedAbstractListTest
    Tests functionality of LinkedAbstractList class
    LinkedListRecursive<E>
    custom implementation of a recursive linked list that doesn't allow for null elements or duplicate elements as defined by the equals() method.
    LinkedListRecursiveTest
    Tests the LinkedListRecursive class
    LinkedQueue<E>
    Implements a Queue on an LinkedAbstractlist and provides functions for adding items to the back of the queue, removing items from the front of the queue, checking if the queue is empty, getting the number of items in the queue, and setting the queue's capacity.
    LinkedQueueTest
    Provides suite of tests for the LinkedQueue Class
    LinkedStack<E>
    Creates a stack based on a LinkedList and provides functions for pushing to the top of the stack, popping the top item off the stack, checking if the stack is empty, getting the number of items on the stack, and setting the stack's capacity.
    LinkedStackTest
    Provides suite of tests for the linkedStack
